14/05/2004
WARSAW, Poland -- Bulgaria will keep its troops in Iraq for as long as they are needed, Foreign Minister Solomon Passy said during a visit to Warsaw on Thursday (13 May). President Georgi Parvanov had already made this commitment during a visit to the soldiers in Iraq in April. Bulgaria has 440 troops in Karbala right now.
In other news, the Committee of Ministers of the Council of Europe adopted a statement Thursday, expressing "grave concern" over the death sentences handed to five Bulgarian nurses in Libya last week. The committee called for an immediate review of the verdict. (AFP - 13/05/04)
